https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/ztJ3Gr27mdQ6f5sPebhfNya2aPd.jpg A revealing look at the great Quebecois director who gave us such classic films as Mon Oncle Antoine, A toute prendre and Kamouraska: Power of Passion. Amidst the rise of French-Canadian identity and the political struggles of the '60s, Jutra was at the forefront of a group of artists dedicated to social change and attacking taboo. Claude Jutra: An Unfinished Story
